The bizarre decision to rule out the goal from Keane, was like a ghost returning to punish the blues, again.
Evertonians with a long memory will recall a far reaching defeat that destroyed the great 1970 championship team
Playing Liverpool in the 1971 FA Cup semi final, the blues lost the lead when goalie Andy Rankin came out for a cross, and just like Reno in this game, he dropped the ball in an aerial challenge with John Toshack, at the feet of Brian Hall who passed into the net,  just like Keane did here.
Its hard to believe the blues would get a decision like this one in their favour, on any away ground in the PL.
Maybe like Howard Kendall's early days when goals were scarce once they begin to hit the target the teams fortunes may change.
When the winger Terry Curran joined Howards squad  in late 1982,  it started opening up goals around that team.
